OL,6,FDuring his speech, Mr Charters raised
OL,7,Fthe case of his constituent, Adam, who
OL,8,F"got into debt through falling behind
OL,9,Fon council tax and card repayments
OL,10,Fafter losing an agency job and
OL,11,Fstruggling to find new work".
OL,13,FHe added: "As is often the case with
OL,14,Frogue bailiffs, the visits were
OL,15,Faggressive and intimidating. One
OL,16,Fforced his foot into the door,
OL,17,Fthreatening to come in and, of course,
OL,18,Fthis breaks virtually every rule in
OL,19,Fthe book.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
